# This directory contains external binaries bundled with the app
#
# macOS ffmpeg binaries
# --------------------
# macOS static ffmpeg binaries are NOT committed to the repository.
# They are downloaded automatically during CI from:
#   https://ffmpeg.martin-riedl.de/redirect/latest/macos/{arch}/release/ffmpeg.zip
#
# For local development, the app falls back to system ffmpeg (see lib.rs
# run_ffmpeg_command). If you need a bundled sidecar locally:
#   1. Download a static ffmpeg build for your platform
#   2. Name it ffmpeg-aarch64-apple-darwin (ARM) or ffmpeg-x86_64-apple-darwin (Intel)
#   3. Place it here and chmod +x
#   4. The .gitignore prevents accidental commits of these binaries
#
# Linux ffmpeg wrappers
# --------------------
# The Linux files (ffmpeg-*-unknown-linux-gnu) are thin shell scripts that
# delegate to system ffmpeg. They ARE tracked in git intentionally.
# Linux bundles expect ffmpeg to be installed on the host system.
